<p>The <code>time</code> function formats a timestamp as time only.</p>

<h2>Basic Usage</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | time{close}</pre>
<p>Current time: <b>{echo {now} | time}</b></p>

<h2>Custom Format</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | time('H:i'){close}</pre>
<p>24-hour: <b>{echo {now} | time('H:i')}</b></p>

<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | time('h:i A'){close}</pre>
<p>12-hour: <b>{echo {now} | time('h:i A')}</b></p>

<h2>With Seconds</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | time('H:i:s'){close}</pre>
<p>With seconds: <b>{echo {now} | time('H:i:s')}</b></p>

<h2>Chained Examples</h2>
<pre>{open}echo {open}now{close} | time('H:i') | bold{close}</pre>
<p>Bold time: {echo {now} | time('H:i') | bold}</p>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>Shortcut for time-only formatting. Use <code>date</code> for full date-time formatting.</p>
